    <note>Yao(1) Guangxiao [35140] He came from a family whose hereditary occupation was medicine. He became a Buddhist priest at age 14 with the ming 道衍 and zi 斯道. In 1404, after advising in court for a number of years, he returned to lay status and was granted the mingzi, Guangxiao and appointed to civil office. MS, 145.4079-4081.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1348:  became a Buddhist priest.</note>
